exports[`serializeText fixture snapshots > serializes simple-text (branches-all) 1`] = `
"Planning a vegetable garden
===========================
Created: 2026-05-14 09:12 UTC · Updated: 2026-05-14 09:13 UTC

────────────────────────
Human

What vegetables grow well in partial shade? I have a north-facing bed that only gets about four hours of sun.

────────────────────────
Claude

Four hours of sun is enough for plenty of crops. Leafy greens and many root vegetables actually prefer some shade.

| Crop | Sun needed | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Lettuce | 3–4 h | Bolts slower in shade |
| Spinach | 3–4 h | Sow early spring |
| Radishes | 4 h | Ready in ~30 days |
| Chard | 4 h | Cut-and-come-again |

A simple sowing plan:

\`\`\`text
March:  spinach, radishes
April:  lettuce, chard
May:    succession-sow lettuce every 2 weeks
\`\`\`

Avoid fruiting crops (tomatoes, peppers, squash) — they need 6–8 hours.
"
`;

exports[`serializeText fixture snapshots > serializes simple-text (defaults) 1`] = `
